-- в”Ђв”Ђ Quaderno в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Automated tax compliance software that calculates, tracks, and reports sales tax, VAT, and GST for online businesses across more than 12,000 tax jurisdictions worldwide, with automatic invoicing and nexus and threshold monitoring.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Tiered monthly subscription based on transaction volume, with a 7-day free trial$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Hobby plan starts at $29 per month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2014, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Roughly 13-17 employees (Quaderno operates as an independent unit within Visma, which it joined in 2023)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Las Palmas, Canary Islands, Spain$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$Spanish$q$, $q$Catalan$q$, $q$Basque$q$, $q$German$q$, $q$French$q$, $q$Italian$q$, $q$Dutch$q$, $q$Portuguese$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Quaderno Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Quaderno review covering the global tax compliance and invoicing software, its pricing plans, key features, pros, cons, and how it fits SaaS and e-commerce businesses.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Quaderno is a tax compliance and automated invoicing platform designed for online businesses, particularly SaaS companies, digital product sellers, and marketplaces that sell across many tax jurisdictions. The company launched in 2014, founded by Carlos, and was self-funded, or bootstrapped, for roughly ten years before joining Visma, one of Europe's largest providers of business-critical cloud software, through an acquisition completed in September 2023. Quaderno continues to operate under its own brand and management as part of the Visma family, headquartered in Las Palmas, in Spain's Canary Islands, with a lean team of roughly 13 to 17 employees. Quaderno's core function is calculating and tracking sales tax, VAT, and GST automatically as transactions occur, drawing on a database that the company says covers more than 12,000 tax jurisdictions worldwide. The platform monitors a business's sales activity against each jurisdiction's registration thresholds and sends nexus and threshold alerts so finance teams know when they are approaching an obligation to register and start collecting tax in a new state or country, a common blind spot for fast-growing digital businesses selling internationally. Beyond tax calculation, Quaderno generates automatic, customizable, and locally compliant invoices and receipts for each transaction, and it offers Quaderno Checkout, a hosted checkout flow that handles tax-compliant billing directly. Multichannel tax reporting consolidates sales tax data across integrated platforms so businesses can file returns without manually reconciling numbers from Stripe, Shopify, or other sales channels. The product connects with common billing and e-commerce tools used by SaaS and platform businesses and provides personalized onboarding assistance to new customers. Quaderno's interface supports at least nine languages, including English, Spanish, Catalan, Basque, German, French, Italian, Dutch, and Portuguese, and automatic invoices are generated in the official language of the customer's country by default. Pricing follows a tiered monthly subscription model based on transaction volume rather than revenue or number of users. The Hobby plan starts at $29 per month for up to 25 transactions and a single user and integration, aimed at very small businesses just starting to sell internationally. The Startup plan is $49 per month for up to 250 transactions with unlimited users, jurisdictions, and integrations; the Business plan is $99 per month for up to 1,000 transactions; and the Growth plan is $149 per month for up to 2,500 transactions, with all plans above Hobby including unlimited users and integrations. Businesses that exceed 2,500 transactions per month move to a custom-quoted Enterprise plan. All paid plans come with a 7-day free trial that requires no credit card, and customers who approach their transaction limit are alerted and automatically upgraded to the next tier rather than being charged unpredictable overage fees. Quaderno is best suited for SaaS companies, digital platforms, and marketplaces that need to stay compliant with sales tax and VAT rules across many countries and states without building in-house tax logic.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '3daa81ad-63b3-4469-9a34-5214e31502af';

